Bill Gates is now the favorite target for coronavirus misinformation according to data compiled by the New York Times and Zignal Labs, a company that analyzes media sources.
The New York Times found 16,000 posts on Facebook this year that were liked and commented on nearly 900,000 times.
The 10 most popular Youtube videos spreading misinformation about Gates and the virus were viewed almost five millions times in March and April.
A Bill Gates speech from 2015, where he warns that the greatest threat to humanity is infectious disease, not nuclear war, has received 25 million new views in recent weeks.
Gates has long been an outspoken critic of President TrumpGates has long been an outspoken critic of President Trump.